<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="81" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1801,2006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1801,1826]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Bothridial setae setiform with unilateral barbulations, integument densely granulated throughout the body, reflective, giving a shiny black appearance. All prodorsal seta present; porose area 
<emphasis box="[1140,1171,1838,1862]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">A2</emphasis>
absent; notogaster with ten pairs of alveoli; dorsosejugal suture interrupted; lyrifissure 
<emphasis box="[852,888,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">iad</emphasis>
situated near anal plate; without medial pore and porose area postanalis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="88" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1801,2006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1945,1970]" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Description.</emphasis>
(N=7) Length of males 443–473 (463), width 335–374 (354); length of females 473–513, width 335–374, height 360–371 of both sexes (364). Color shiny black, a clear coppery lenticular area present.
</paragraph>
