<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="88" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,583,608]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName box="[581,691,583,608]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsidiana">
<emphasis box="[581,691,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">obsidiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the color and brightness similar to volcanic obsidian stone.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="88" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,655,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,591,655,680]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsidiana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[329,591,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">Pergalumna obsidiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[606,702,655,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[606,696,655,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a strong resemblance to 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1283,655,680]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypergranulosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1071,1283,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">P. hypergranulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1296,1394,655,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1296,1394,655,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by integumentary granulation, shape and position of porose areas and bothridial setae 
<emphasis box="[1105,1130,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">bs</emphasis>
, however it may be easily differentiated by the shape and ornamentation of genital plates, interlamellar setae (
<emphasis box="[1144,1166,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">in</emphasis>
) inserted in 
<emphasis box="[1322,1338,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">L</emphasis>
margin, presence of a rostral sclerotic extension, subcapitulum with anterior apex bilobed and more intense and shiny dark coloration. Furthermore, it differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[597,746,799,824]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulatus">
<emphasis box="[597,746,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">P. granulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by barbulate 
<emphasis box="[900,925,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">bs</emphasis>
in only one side and protuberances in genital plates, from 
<taxonomicName box="[295,493,836,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatiporosa">
<emphasis box="[295,493,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">P. elongatiporosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of 
<emphasis box="[686,717,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">A1</emphasis>
, from 
<taxonomicName box="[797,1007,836,861]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralongisetosa">
<emphasis box="[797,1007,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">P. paralongisetosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having heavier granulation on the notogaster and from 
<taxonomicName box="[383,506,871,896]" class="Arachnida" family="Galumnidae" genus="Pergalumna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvatica">
<emphasis box="[383,506,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="88">P. silvatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by four notogastric porose areas.
</paragraph>
